Nigerian musician, David Adeleke, popularly known as Davido on Friday announced the postponement of his North American music tour. Davido, who made the announcement via his official Twitter page, said postponing his North America music tour scheduled for April/March was the right thing to do to ensure the heath and safety of his staff and fans. He said, “I’m saddened to halt what has been a fantastic sold-out tour so far, but postponing is the right thing to do. “The health and safety of my fans and staff is most paramount and nothing else matters. Be safe and see you all soon! God be with us all! Since corona virus broke out it Wahun, China in January, it increasing spread across Asia, Europe and African countries has lead to cancellation of major global events.